Parameters:-->
	Also known as functional parameters or method parametrs
	=> Parameters change state of method behaviour
	
	Advantages of parameters:-->
		=> Avoid hardcode progrmming
		=> Method reusability [Instead of writing duplicate methods
				we can reuse same method with differnet input values]
		=> Flexibility [Method accept different parameter values]
		=> Code optimization [Optimize code into less lines]
		
		Parameter types:-->
		
				1. CallByValue
				2. CallByReferrence
				
		CallByvalue:-->
				Passing datatypes as parameters is called callbyvalues
				
				
				public class RobotA
				{
					//Method without parameters
					void Walk()
					{
						int kmps=10;
						System.out.println(kmps);
					}
				
					void Run(int speed)
					{
						System.out.println(speed);
					}
					
					public static void main(String args[])
					{
							RobotA obj=new RobotA();
							obj.Walk();   //No arguments passing because method don't have parameters
							obj.Run(15);  //passing Integer argument
							obj.Run(25);
					}
				
				}
